_search: search index=_internal | head 10 | countmatches fieldname=word_count pattern=\\w+ uri
_remote_search: litsearch index=_internal | fields  keepcolorder=t "*" "_bkt" "_cd" "_si" "host" "index" "linecount" "source" "sourcetype" "splunk_server" "uri,word_count" | prehead  limit=10 null=false keeplast=false
_normalized_search: litsearch index=_internal | fields keepcolorder=t "*" "_bkt" "_cd" "_si" "host" "index" "linecount" "source" "sourcetype" "splunk_server" "uri,word_count" | prehead limit=10 null=false keeplast=false
vix_families:
<root>
  <add_ons>
    <add_on name="hadoop" type="external_results_provider">
      <parameter key="erp_type" value="report"/>
      <parameter key="max_nodes" value="50"/>
    </add_on>
  </add_ons>
</root>

msg: The 'countmatches' command is implemented as an external script and may cause the search to be significantly slower.
